<br>
That's all in your head.<br>
<br>
It's the ratio that's lagging is all. And the proc is supposed to help make up for the ratio and maintain good DPS.<br>
<br>
I'd say it's a better taunt weapon than a Lamentation, which for some odd reason gets used a LOT more by warriors than a Jade Mace, which is faster and better ratio.<br>
<br>
You know, speaking of Jade Mace, it always boggled my mind how people would wonder that my monk drew aggro when he was wielding a Jade Mace/SoS combo, and they were wielding a Lammy/Centi combo.<br>
<br>
That's the thing though. Black Blade of Tormenting fills that nice from your Lammy/Centi days to your WC/Frosty days. It's a step towards keeping aggro a bit better.<br>
<br>
Though levels do that too, Heh.<br>
<br>
